IMPACTWorld+ (Default_Endpoint). Version 1.4IMPACT World+, is the update of the IMPACT 2002+, LUCAS, and EDIP methods.Most of the regional impact categories have been spatially resolved (a specific flow for each region) and all the long-term impact categories have been temporally resolved: short-term damages (over the 100 years after the emission) have been differentiated from long-term damages. Included categories:Human health: •	Global warming, long-term, human health•	Global warming, short-term, human health•	Human toxicity cancer, long-term•	Human toxicity cancer, short-term•	Human toxicity non-cancer , long-term•	Human toxicity non-cancer , short-term•	Ionizing radiation, human health•	Ozone layer depletion•	Particulate matter formation•	Photochemical oxidant formation•	Water availability, human healthEcosystem quality:•	Freshwater acidification•	Freshwater ecotoxicity, long-term•	Freshwater ecotoxicity, short-term•	Freshwater eutrophication•	Global warming, long-term, ecosystem•	Global warming, short-term, ecosystem•	Ionizing radiation, fre. ecosystem•	Land occupation, biodiversity•	Land transformation, biodiversity•	Marine acidification, long-term•	Marine acidification, short-term•	Marine eutrophication•	Terrestrial acidification•	Thermally polluted water•	Water availability, fre. ecosystem•	Water availability, ter. ecosystemRelease date: fev-2017info@impactworldplus.org
